<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880405-0157 </DOCNO><HL> Ply-Gem Industries 6.1% Stake Is Acquired By Firm Based in Spain </HL><SO> </SO><CO> PGI </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Esfinco Inc., a closely held investment firm based in Madrid, Spain, said it holds 6.1% of Ply-Gem Industries Inc.'s common shares outstanding and might seek representation on Ply-Gem's board.    In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, Esfinco said it acquired the stock for investment purposes and might request that one of its representatives be elected to Ply-Gem's board.    According to the filing, Esfinco holds 653,900 Ply-Gem common shares, including 155,000 purchased from March 7 to March 31 for $12.75 to $14.25 a share.    In American Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Ply-Gem shares closed up 62.5 cents, at $14.50.    Ply-Gem, a New York maker of home-improvement products, said it is pleased with Esfinco's investment. </TEXT></DOC>